                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18180909-220-viclabel1208" type="occupation">painter and glazier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-220-victim1676 t18180909-220-viclabel1208"></join>. On the 22d of August, I was in Dean-street, Westminster, going home; when I got to the corner of <placeName id="t18180909-220-crimeloc1209">Orchard-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-220-crimeloc1209" type="placeName" value="Orchard-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-220-crimeloc1209" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-220-off1206 t18180909-220-crimeloc1209"></join>, the prisoner snatched my chain and seals, and ran on-the chain broke. I pursued and collared him in St. Ann's-lane, and asked him for my property, he denied having it. I said he must, or else he had thrown it away. A watchman came up, and took him; another watchman brought my chain and seals. I am certain he is the man; he was never out of my sight. Nobody else was in the street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-220-person1678">
